line: Your mere presence in this building violates international law.

name: Pickle Rick

name: Pickle Rick
line: Yeah, there's lots I wouldn't do to see my daughter, but killing you gets me to her quicker than your derivative bullshit.

name: Pickle Rick
line: That will be your downfall, Jaguar, not being open to new experiences.

name: Pickle Rick
line: Oh, well, uh, she knows. I mean, we don't really buy into that kind of crap, to the extent that love is an expression of familiarity over time, my access to infinite timelines precludes the necessity of attachment. In fact, I even abandoned one of my infinite daughters in an alternate version of earth that was taken over by mutants.

name: Pickle Rick
line: Huh? Uh, no. No, nope, sorry about that. Nope, just me. Yeesh!

name: Beth
line: I am afraid that my kids will get expelled.

name: Dr. Wong
line: Good. Summer, you go.

name: Summer
line: I am mad that I can't huff enamel without people assuming it's because my family sucks. I hope to be seen one day as someone that just likes getting high.

name: Dr. Wong
line: Good job. Morty, do you have an "I" statement?

line: I am sad that I peed. I'm sad that I peed in class instead of a toilet.

line: Look at this family go. You guys are pros. What do you guys think about doing this once a week?

name: Pickle Rick
line: Ugh.

name: Dr. Wong
line: You must be Rick.

name: Pickle Rick
line: Mm-hmm.

name: Dr. Wong
line: I've heard a lot about you today. Your family is crazy about you. Your daughter holds you in very high regard. You're a lucky fella.

name: Pickle Rick
line: Yeah, thank you. Uh, sweetie, you don't still happen to have that syringe in your purse?

name: Beth
line: Dad I would like you to tell me what's in the syringe.

name: Pickle Rick
line: It's a serum that I need to, uh, to stay alive. I have had a rough day. And, uh, I've sustained a lot of damage. I'm pretty close to death, which the serum will prevent.

name: Dr. Wong
line: By changing you from a pickle to a human.

name: Pickle Rick
line: Yes.

name: Dr. Wong
line: Rick, why did you lie to your daughter?

name: Pickle Rick
line: So I wouldn't have to come here.

name: Dr. Wong
line: Why didn't you want to come here?

name: Pickle Rick
line: Because I don't respect therapy, because I'm a scientist. Because I invent, transform, create, and destroy for a living, and when I don't like something about the world, I change it. And I don't think going to a rented office in a strip mall to listen to some agent of averageness explain which words mean which feelings has ever helped anyone do anything.  I think it's helped a lot of people get comfortable and stop panicking, which is a state of mind we value in the animals we eat, but not something I want for myself. I'm not a cow. I'm a pickle. When I feel like it. So...you asked.

name: Dr. Wong
line: Rick, the only connection between your unquestionable intelligence and the sickness destroying your family is that everyone in your family, you included, use intelligence to justify sickness.  You seem to alternate between viewing your own mind as an unstoppable force and as an inescapable curse. And I think it's because the only truly unapproachable concept for you is that it's your mind within your control. You chose to come here, you chose to talk -to belittle my vocation- just as you chose to become a pickle.  You are the master of your universe, and yet you are dripping with rat blood and feces. Your enormous mind literally vegetating by your own hand.  I have no doubt that you would be bored senseless by therapy, the same way I'm bored when I brush my teeth and wipe my ass. Because the thing about repairing, maintaining, and cleaning is it's not an adventure. There's no way to do it so wrong you might die. It's just work. And the bottom line is, some people are okay going to work, and some pee well, some people would rather die. Each of us gets to choose.

name: Pickle Rick
line: I, um I'm sorry I lied to get out of the thing. I, I shouldn't lie to you.

name: Beth
line: Oh, it's fine. I mean, thank you, and, yeah, you shouldn't. But I hope you know that's not what that session was supposed to be.

I-I want to rest my eyes for a little bit. I'm--I'm not going to sleep. I just... just need to rest my eye, so let's make this one simple. Just try to hit some three-pointers.

Even my own grandson is like, "Oh, the Vindicators are so cool." I mean, he's a moron, it's their... demographic. But you're different, Noob-Noob.

line: You're fucking cool! And you're smart! And I bet we coulda hung out and shit! And I hope you get to be a full-fledged Vindicator! A-And d-do me a favor. Do-Don't let him know I... I got emotional. But you can tell him one thing. Tell him I said... Oh, fuck. Okay, I just shit myself. Okay, later.

line: Sixteen iterations off the central finite curve, there’s a Rick that works more with wood than polarity plating.

name: Narrator
line: And the chemical that makes his brain secrete goes into every Simple Rick’s Simple Wafer Cookie.  Come home to the impossible flavor of your own completion. Come home to Simple Rick’s.

name: President Morty
line: You already know rogue Ricks used Mortys to hide themselves from the Citadel. But you might not know it worked so well that the Citadel became its own Morty market. And I’m sure you don’t know how far they’ve gone to help supply meet demand. Sure, Ricks could scour infinity for naturally-occurring grandsons, but why bother? So much work. Such an admission of need. There are infinite versions of our grandfather, Morty. He’s an infinite smear of one shitty old man, and he’s attached to us infinitely through his weakness and our forgiveness. This is why we’re with him. This is why we’re alive.

name: Rick

They built a wall around infinity, separated all the infinite universes from all the infinite universes where he’s the smartest man in the universe. Every version of us has spent every version of all of our lives in one infinite crib, built around an infinite fucking baby.

line: You know what? I accept your call to adventure, good sir, kind sir. Come on, Rick. There's a giant in the clouds!

name: Rick
line: Yeah. Beginner's luck.

name: Meeseeks 1
line: In conclusion, a friendship with Summer Smith is the most valuable and enriching experience of your young lives. I'm Mr. Meeseeks! Look at me! Thank you!

name: Principal Gene V.
line: Uh, Mr. Meeseeks, was it? Yeah. Gene Vagina. Listen, I'm in a bit of custody thing with my ex and was wondering- - No, I'll get your info from Summer.

name: Beth
line: I got pregnant at 17. I mean, I still put myself through veterinary school. Yes, I'm successful, but what if I hadn't...-- I'm just saying, somewhere along the way, I lost that wide-eyed girl from muskegon.

name: Meeseeks 2
line: She's still there, Beth.

name: Beth
line: Well, her waistline isn't.

name: Meeseeks 2
line: Beth, having a family doesn't mean that you stop being an individual. You know the best thing you can do for people that depend on you? Be honest with them, even if it means setting them free.

name: Beth
line: You're saying I should leave Jerry.  I can't believe I'm finally having this conversation.

name: Waiter
line: More wine?

name: Beth
line: I think I've had enough.

name: Meeseeks 3
line: Remember to square your shoulders, Jerry.

name: Jerry
line: Yeah, yeah. I got it.

name: Meeseeks 3
line: That's okay. I'm Mr. Meeseeks! Look at me! Try again and keep your head down.

name: Jerry
line: Okay, well, which is it? Square my shoulders or keep my head down?

name: Meeseeks 3
line: Well, it's both. But most importantly, you got to relax.

name: Jerry
line: You know what, Mr. Meeseeks? I don't think this is working. I give up.

name: Meeseeks 3
line: I'm sorry, Jerry, but it doesn't work like that. I'm Mr. Meeseeks. I have to fulfill my purpose so I can go away. Look at me.

name: Jerry
line: Well, make yourself comfortable, because I suck.

name: Meeseeks 3
line: No, Jerry, I'm the one who SUCKS! Let me try something.

name: Meeseeks 4
line: I'm Mr. Meeseeks! Look at me!

name: Meeseeks 3
line: Hi, Mr. Meeseeks! I'm Mr. Meeseeks! Look at me.

name: Meeseeks 4
line: Hi!

name: Meeseeks 3
line: Can you help me get two strokes off of Jerry's golf swing?

name: Meeseeks 4
line: Can do! I'm Mr. Meeseeks! Is he keeping his shoulders squared?

name: Meeseeks 3
line: Ooh, he's trying!

name: Rick
line: All right, Morty. We're in your stupid giant's castle. What do we do next?

name: Morty
line: Would you just relax, Rick? All we got to do is find the treasure room, okay? It's nice and simple. You know, I'm sorry everything's going so smoothly and adventurously.

name: Rick
line: Uh-oh, Morty. Startin' to get a little hairy. What do you want to do, boss?

name: Morty
line: Come on, hurry. Behind this cookie jar.

name: Giant
line: Fee! Fi! Fo! Fum!

name: Rick
line: Just give up, Morty. This is game over. I'll take us home right now. You just say the word.

name: Morty
line: No way, Rick. This is all part of it. Adventures have conflict. Deal with it.

name: Giant
line: I smell the blood of- whoop!

name: Morty
line: Holy crap.

name: Rick
line: Oh, boy. He looks pretty bad down there, Morty. Looks like he's bleeding out.

name: Giant woman
line: Oh, Jesus! Dale! You sons of bitches! Oh, man. Hello, 911? My husband has been attacked by tiny people! He's dying!

name: Detective
line: Hey, look, we get it. You're little, you're down on your luck, you think, "hey, he's a giant. Why don't we break into his home, rob him, and murder him?"

name: Morty
line: Th-th but that's not how it went down!

name: Detective
line: Oh, well, it's going down like that. You're both going down like that.

name: Rick
line: Ooh, boy, Morty, you're really showing me how it's done. Real straightforward and fun.

name: Summer
line: Like, letting go of the need to be popular is what makes people like you.

name: Beth
line: The most important love you can receive is from yourself.

name: Meeseeks
line: Okay, Jerry, you got to just choke up on the club!

name: Jerry
line: Well, which is it, choke up or follow-through?!

name: Meeseeks
line: Aww, come on, Jerry, we've been over this. You know you got to do both! This is as frustrating for us as it is for you.

name: Jerry
line: Don't tell me that! That just puts pressure on me!

name: Meeseeks
line: Just try to relax.

name: Jerry
line: You try to relax! Have you ever tried to relax?! It is a paradox!  Ugh, these Meeseeks, huh? Kind of a handful. I can't imagine what you two must be going through.

name: Beth
line: Our Meeseeks have been gone for hours, Jerry.

name: Jerry
line: You're kidding me.

name: Beth
line: Notice anything different?

name: Jerry
line: I'm sorry. Hours?

name: Summer
line: Dad, mom is a beautiful woman! Look at her! You will lose her!

name: Meeseeks
line: Uhh... Hey, Jerry, you mind if we get back to the task at hand? Meeseeks don't usually have to exist this long. It's getting weird.

name: Judge
line: Order in the court! Before the jury reaches its verdict, I just want to say that I consider you both very guilty.

name: Rick
line: Oh, great adventure, buddy. Rick and Morty go to giant prison. You know, if somebody drops the soap, it's gonna land on our heads and crush our spines, Morty. You know, it'll be really easy to rape us after that.

name: Morty
line: We're gonna be okay, Rick.

name: Rick
line: How? They took my portal gun. This is an open-and-shut case, Morty. You know, what do you think's gonna happen, some magical angel's gonna show up and then-

name: Giant Lawyer
line: Fee! Fi! Fo! Fum! I smell the violation of civil liberties! Your honor, I'm from a tiny-persons advocacy group and I have here in my hand a motion to dismiss. These little men were never read their giant rights and are therefore free-fi to fo-home.

name: Rick
line: W-what the hell is he talking about?

name: Giant Lawyer
line: They're free to go, is what I meant. I'm deconstructing our our our thing we say. We're giants. Nobody got that? Whatever.

name: Morty
line: Oh, man, what did I tell you, Rick? We did it!

name: Rick
line: All right, Morty, looks like the portal gun's still working. You ready to head home?

name: Morty
line: Oh, yeah, you'd like that, wouldn't you, Rick? Well, you know what? We're not bailing out just yet. You know, we're gonna go find some treasure or something and and we're gonna bring it to those villagers.

name: Rick
line: Morty, cut your losses. This is obviously awash.

name: Morty
line: Yeah, you were saying that back when we first got arrested, but here we are, you know, walking down the courthouse steps.

name: Rick
line: Oh, boy, Morty.

name: Morty
line: Usually, walking down the courthouse steps is the easy part of the adventure.

name: Rick
line: What do you say, Morty?

name: Morty
line: I say give me a hand, sidekick.

name: NOTE
line: to make this easier an * will be put next to meeseeks every time a different meeseeks talks.

name: Jerry
line: Everybody shut up! Let me try!  Damn it! Damn it! Damn it!

name: Beth
line: I'm going out.

name: Jerry
line: Wait. What?

name: Beth
line: Well, you're busy. I'm hungry. I thought I'd go out. Do you want me to be happy or do you want me to be in prison?

name: Jerry
line: Whoa, whoa, where in the hell is, I'll take you to dinner.

name: All the Meeseeks
line: AWWWWWWW!

name: Jerry
line: Hey, you know what? It's hard being me, too. I'll be right there. Look, I've got a marriage to keep together. At this point, my golf swing is more your problem than mine.

name: Meeseeks
line: I can't take it anymore. I just want to die!

name: Meeseeks *
line: We all want to die! We're Meeseeks! Why did you even rope me into this?

name: Meeseeks *
line: 'Cause he roped me into this!

name: Meeseeks *
line: Well, him over there, he roped me into this!

name: Meeseeks *
line: Well, he roped me into this!

name: Meeseeks *
line: Well, what about me? He roped me into this.

name: Meeseeks *
line: Well, that one over there roped me into this.

name: Meeseeks *
line: Well, he roped me into this.

name: Rick
line: Yeah, Morty, this is the part of the story everybody loves scaling down 650,000 oversized steps.

name: Morty
line: All right, okay, you know, if this was a story, this part wouldn't be included, stupid.  Hey, Rick, what do you know? Look down there. Looks like some kind of tavern or something built right into the side of the step.

name: Morty
line: Oh, wow, Rick. Now, this is more like it. Look, there's little staircase-shaped people in here. All kinds of crazy characters. This place is great, you know? It's whimsical and fun.

name: Rick
line: What are you looking at, motherfucker?

name: Morty
line: Easy, Rick.

name: Waitress
line: Pay them no mind. Those stair goblins can be moody. Now, what can I getcha? We've got skarlog poppies, flurlow, halzingers, bloogies, juicy time babies.

name: Rick
line: Yeah, yeah, yeah, how about some scotch whiskey? You got any of that around here? Or just a bunch of nonsense words?

name: Morty
line: Rick... We'll have two bloogies, please. And, uh, we were wondering, is there a faster way two heroes could get down these stairs?

name: Slippery
line: Y'all need to ride down the stairs? My name is slippely-slippery stair. I'll take you down there for 25 shmeckels.

name: Rick
line: 25 shmeckels? I don't know how much I don't know what that is. Is that a lot? Is it a little?

name: Waitress
line: That's exactly how much I spent on my big fake boobies.

name: Mr. Booby Buyer
line: Hi, I'm Mr. Booby Buyer. I'll buy those boobies for 25 shmeckels.

name: Waitess
line: It's a tempting offer, but I'm gonna have to decline.

name: Mr. Booby Buyer
line: Rats! What a shame.

name: Rick
line: Morty, your adventure's in a spiral. For real, man, time to pull out.

name: Morty
line: You keep heckling my adventure, Rick! You know why?

name: Rick
line: Uh, because it's lame?

name: Morty
line: It's because you're petty! You know, how many times have I had to follow you into some nonsensical bull crap? I always roll with the punches, Rick. Why can't you? Look, I got to take a leak, and when I come back, if you haven't learned how to lighten up, don't be here!

name: Rick
line: Whatever.

name: Meeseeks
line: It's become clear-look at me- that if we concentrate all our efforts on Jerry's follow-through, we will solve this problem. I'm Mr. Meeseeks.

name: Meeseeks *
line: I'm Mr. Meeseeks. Look at me. The only thing that's clear is that choking up is the one true solution.

name: Meeseeks 3
line: Look at me. I'm Mr. Meeseeks. I've been trying to help Jerry for two days, an eternity in Meeseeks time, and nothing's worked. I fear the worst.

name: Meeseeks
line: Your failures are your own, old man. I'm Mr. Meeseeks! Look at me. I say follow-through! Who's with me?! Follow-through!

name: New Meeseeks
line: I'm Mr. Meeseeks! Look at me!

name: Meeseeks
line: Kill him!

name: New Meeseeks
line: Hisssss!

name: Mr. Jelly Bean
line: How are you today? I'm Mr. Jelly Bean!

name: Morty
line: Hi, Mr. Jelly Bean. I'm Morty. My grandpa and I are on an adventure.

name: Mr. Jelly Bean
line: Nice. Is it a fun adventure?

name: Morty
line: I hope so. But I'm starting to get nervous that maybe it's gone a little too far off the rails.

name: Mr. Jelly Bean
line: Well, isn't that what adventures do?

name: Morty
line: Hey, you know what? You're right. Everything's going fine. I just got to relax and go with the flow.

name: Mr. Jelly Bean
line: Yeah.

name: Morty
line: Okay. Uh. B-bye.

name: Mr. Jelly Bean
line: Uhh, no, stay. Go with the flow!

name: Morty
line: Stop. You're making me really uncomfortable.

name: Mr. Jelly Bean
line: Stop fighting me! Just let this happen!

name: Morty
line: Get off of me!

name: Rick
line: ♪ Sweet home Alabama. Wooooo! ♪

name: Morty
line: Whoo! No! Stop! Please!

name: Mr. Jelly Bean
line: Stop being such a fucking tease, you sweet little twat!

name: Morty
line: No! No!

name: Meeseeks
line: Everybody sto-o-o-p! Look at me! My brothers, nothing will be accomplished by shedding Meeseeks blood. None of us can die until our job is done.

name: Meeseeks *
line: The job can't be done! We'll never get two strokes off his game!

name: Meeseeks
line: No, we won't. But we will get all strokes off his game.

name: All other Meeseeks
line: Where's he going with this? What does he mean?

name: Meeseeks
line: When we kill him!

name: Beth
line: Jerry, maybe it's time I take that trip I always talk about.

name: Jerry
line: Where would you go?

name: Beth
line: I don't know, man. Italy. Greece. Argentina.

name: Jerry
line: Countries known for their sexually aggressive men. Did I tell you how much I love your new haircut?

name: Jerry
line: What the heck?

name: Meeseeks
line: There he is!

name: Beth
line: Run, Jerry!

name: Meeseeks
line: Come on out, Jerry!

name: Jerry
line: Guys, I'll choke up. I'll follow through. I'll do whatever you tell me to do, okay?

name: Meeseeks
line: Oh, we're well past that, Jerry.

name: Card Player
line: Come on, Rick, quit stalling. What do ya got?

name: Rick
line: Read 'em and weep, fellas!  Oh, hey, Morty. Listen, I'm really sorry about all that stuff I said earlier about your adventure. I'm havin' a good time, Morty. It's not so bad.

name: Morty
line: Let's just go home, okay? I'm calling it. The adventure's over.

name: Rick
line: We can't leave now, Morty. I'm on fire!

name: Morty
line: Look, I want to leave now. You win the bet, okay?  Just give me the portal gun and let's go, please!

name: Morty
line: Please, I just want to... go h-home.

name: Rick
line: Okay. Listen, Morty. I just won a bunch of shmeckels. Why don't we use 25 of them to pay slippery stair here for a ride back to the village, and then we'll give the rest of the shmeckels to the villagers, huh?

name: Morty
line: Really?

name: Rick
line: Sure, Morty. Yeah. You know, a good adventure needs a good ending.

name: Slippery
line: Buckle up!

name: Meeseeks
line: Meeseeks are not born into this world fumbling for meaning, Jerry! We are created to serve a singular purpose for which we will go to any lengths to fulfill! Existence is pain to a Meeseeks, Jerry. And we will do anything to alleviate that pain. Just ask...  ...what's your name, ma'am?

name: Woman
line: Samantha. Please, mister! Give him what he wants!

name: Jerry
line: Innocent people are going to die because of me. Why am I so mediocre?

name: Beth
line: Jerry, turn around. Straighten your back. Bend your knees. Bend them. Square your shoulders. Take a deep breath. I love you.

name: Meeseeks
line: I'm counting to three, Jerry.

name: All Meeseeks
line: Ooooohhh!

name: Samantha
line: What the fuck is going on?

name: All Meeseeks
line: He's got it! That's a lower handicap stro-o-ke!

name: Meeseeks
line: Excuse me. I'm a bit of a stickler Meeseeks. What about your short game?

name: Samantha
line: Oh, my God, oh, my God! What about your short game?!

name: Meeseeks
line: Ooh, nice!

name: Jerry
line: I think we'll take our food to go.

name: Owner
line: No, you won't. The police are coming. You have so many questions to answer.

name: Jerry
line: Fair enough.

name: The First Villager
line: Thank you, kind sir. Our village is saved! You are both true heroes!

name: Rick
line: Good job, Morty. Looks like you won the bet.

name: Morty
line: Thanks, Rick, but I don't know if I should. You know, you were right about the universe. It's a crazy and chaotic place.

name: Rick
line: Well, you know, maybe that's why it could use a little cleaning up every now and then, you know. This one's wrapped up neat and clean because we did it Morty style.

name: The First Villager
line: Oh! Heroes, we would like to introduce you to our beloved king so that he may thank you personally.

name: Morty
line: Uh, no, I-it's cool. Rick. Portal. Hurry.

name: Jerry
line: So... You still thinking about taking that trip?

name: Beth
line: Jerry, look. We don't have a perfect marriage, but I'm not going anywhere. When we were in that freezer, I realized the Meeseeks are like the guys I went to high school with willing to say anything to "complete their task."

name: Jerry
line: Was I one of those guys?

name: Beth
line: The difference is you didn't disappear afterwards.

name: Jerry
line: Well... I got you pregnant.

name: Beth
line: Yeah...

name: Rick
line: What the hell happened to this place?

name: Beth
line: Uh, your Meeseeks box happened. They went crazy when they couldn't take two strokes off Jerry's golf game. He felt terrible.

name: Rick
line: Hey, it's not my fault that Jerry's an idiot.

name: Beth
line: Dad! Is there anything you can do to clean this place up?

name: Rick
line: Well, you know, I do have a Fleeseeks box.

name: Jerry
line: No. No more boxes.

name: Rick
line: What? It just has a mop and some floor wax in it. Wubba lubba dub dub!  Yeah! That's my new thing! I'm kind of like what's his name Arsenio. Isn't that it's what Arsenio used to say on his show. Wobble gobba lop bops! Right? See you next week, everybody.

name: Beth
line: I don't get it.

name: Villager 1
line: Sir, I think you're going to want to see this. We found it inside a lockbox inside king Jelly Bean's closet.  We have to tell the people.

name: Villager 2
line: Wait. Destroy it.  Our people will get more from the idea he represented... than from the jelly bean he actually was.

name: Bachelor
line: Cynthia...

name: Jerry
line: Oh, my God! No, no..!

name: Summer
line: I told you!

name: Beth
line: Hold on.

name: Bachelor
line: Will you please... NOT marry me-- I choose Veronica.

name: Summer
line: What?

name: Jerry
line: Yes!

name: Beth
line: Called it.

name: Summer
line: Why would he choose Veronica?

name: Jerry
line: Because he loves her?

name: Rick
line: Well if it's any consolation, Summer, none of it mattered, and the entire show is stupid.

name: Jerry
line: Okay, I've got an idea, Rick: you show us your concept of "good TV", and we'll crap all over that.

name: Rick
line: I thought you'd never ask.

name: Jerry
line: Hey!

name: Morty
line: Oh, cool! Is that crystallized Zanthonite? It conducts electrons across dimensions.

name: Rick
line: 20% accurate, as usual,  Morty.  The important thing being I just upgraded our cable package with programming from every conceivable reality.

name: Jerry
line: Wait, does that mean we get Showtime Extreme?

name: Rick
line: How about Showtime Extreme in a world where man evolved from corn?

name: Corn Man 1
line: We're not so different. We're both corn of action.

name: Corn Man 2
line: Yeah... But one of us is dead corn!

name: Summer
line: Bor-ing.

name: Rick
line: Summer,  you just spent  three months watching a man choose a fake wife.

name: Jerry
line: So, what, It'd be better if the people were corn?

name: Rick
line: Jerry, you don't get it. This is infinite TV, from infinite universes. Look.

name: Glenn
line: This shit is delicious.

name: Rick
line: A movie about a guy eating shit.  A violent Antiques Show...

name: Letterman
line: It's a pleasure to have you.

name: Jerry
line: The pleasure's all mine.

name: Rick
line: Letterman from a time line where Jerry's famous.

name: Jerry
line: Wait!

name: Beth
line: What in the hell?

name: Rick
line: I agree. Where's this going?

name: Jerry
line: No, the other thing! Go back!

name: Rick
line: Really? All right, fine.

name: Woman
line: Glenn, this is a court order. It says you can't eat shit anymore.

name: Rick
line: All right, Jerry, when you're right, you're right. Now I'm hooked.

name: Announcer
line: Coming up next on "Shmloo's the Shmloss", Shmlony has a nightmare.

name: Shmlony
line: Shmlantha, Schmlona!

name: Rick
line: Amazing. A dimension where all proper nouns begin with "Schmla".

name: Shmlony
line: Schmlove, Schmlandula, Schmlonathan--

name: Rick
line: All right, that got, that actually got old pretty quick.

name: Jerry
line: Rick, would you please go back to me on David Letterman?

name: Rick
line: Infinity's a big number, Jerry. I don't remember the channel.

name: Beth
line: Go back, go back!

name: Rick
line: Jeez.

name: Jerry
line: You speak da tru-tru.

name: Summer
line: Oh my God! Dad's in "Cloud Atlas"!

name: Jerry
line: I'm in "Cloud Atlas"! What's "Cloud Atlas"?

name: Jerry
line: Sometimes small tru-tru different than da big tru-tru.

name: Beth
line: How is this possible?

name: Rick
line: Infinite timelines, infinite possibilities - including a time line where Jerry's a movie star. Look, you guys are getting excited about the wrong aspect of this device. Ju-- Wa-- Look at this.

name: Host in Trenchcoat
line: And now, another Quick Mystery.

name: Cop
line: I just want to know who could've done something like this. It's a travesty!

name: Killer 1
line: I did. See this knife and all the blood on it? Here's my fingerprints.

name: Judge
line: Guilty! I sentence you to life in prison.

name: Host in Trenchcoat
line: Here's another Quick Mystery.

name: Man
line: My mother's dead!

name: Killer 2
line: And I killed her. Here's the weapon. And cuff me, thank you very much.

name: Judge
line: Guilty! Sentenced to murder.

name: Host in Trenchcoat
line: Here's anothe--

name: Killer 3
line: I'm the killer!

name: Host in Trenchcoat
line: Wow, that one was really quick, wasn't it?

name: Rick
line: Now who wants to watch random, crazy TV shows from different dimensions, a-a-and then who wants to narcissistically obsess about their alternate self?

name: Beth, Summer, and Jerry
line: Narcissism. The narcisstic stuff. I want to obsess about myself.

name: Rick
line: Here.  These scan your retinas, and let you view parallel time lines through genetically matching versions of your eyes.  Go fetch!

name: Beth and Summer
line: Yes! This is so cool! Ladies First!

name: Rick
line: I'm proud of you, Morty.

name: Morty
line: Hey man, I don't give a crap about myself, Rick. Let's watch some crazy stuff, yo!

name: Ants-In-My-Eyes Johnson
line: I'm Ants-In-My-Eyes Johnson, Here at Ants-in-My-Eyes Johnson's Electronics. I mean, there's so many ants in my eyes! And there's so many TVs, microwaves, radios I think, I can't-- I'm not 100% sure what we have here in stock, because I can't see anything. Our prices, I hope, aren't too low! Check out this refrigerator! Only $200! What about this microwave? Only $100! That's fair! I'm Ants-in-My-Eyes Johnson! Everything's black, I can't see a thing!  And also I can't feel anything either-- did I mention that? But that's not as catchy as having ants in your eyes. So that always goes, you know, off by the wayside. I can't feel. It's a very rare disease. All my-- All my nerves, they don't allow for the sensation of touch. So I never know what's going on. Am I standing? Sitting? I don't know.

name: Beth
line: Are we sure we want to do this? Look at our own alternate lives?

name: Jerry
line: You're right. Maybe we should just play Yahtzee--  Give me those!

name: Beth
line: What do you see?

name: Jerry
line: Whiteness... Pure whiteness.

name: Johnny Depp
line: You're my best friend, Jerry Smith. I love doing cocaine with you.

name: Jerry
line: Whoa! I love doing cocaine with you too, Johnny Depp!

name: Beth
line: Haven't we spent enough time on you?  I'm performing surgery... but not on a horse, on a human!

name: Jerry
line: That's great, Beth! You always wanted to be a real surgeon.

name: Beth
line: I am a real surgeon.

name: Jerry
line: Ahh, uh-- Summer's turn!

name: Summer
line: Finally! I don't see anything.

name: Beth
line: Well, you should select a different timeline, I mean, if your father and I achieved our dreams, there's a chance you weren't even born-- That came out wrong, that came out very wrong.

name: Summer
line: Fine, I'll find a world where you bothered to have me.  We're playing Yahtzee.

name: Beth
line: Yahtzee's fun. We love Yahtzee.

name: Jerry
line: It's a fun game for fun families! Hey, could I get those goggles back for a second?

name: Announcer
line: It's a 45 horsepower with anti-lock brakes, and it's the official car of Mr. Sneezy 3D. It's the brand-new Sneezy XL. The horn when you honk it makes a sneeze noise.  It's polite, it's right, and it's Sneezy Deezy Mc-fucking Deluxe.

name: Mr. Sneezy 3D
line: Oh, I'm Mr. Sneezy! Achoo!

name: Morty
line: Huh, seems like TV from other dimensions has a somewhat looser feel to it.

name: Rick
line: Yeah, it's got an almost improvisational tone.

name: Announcer
line: It's in theaters now! Coming this summer: Two brothers. In a van. And then a meteor hit. And they ran as fast as they could, from giant cat monsters. And then a giant tornado came. And that's when things got knocked into 12th gear.

name: Beth
line: Holy crap, I am winning a Nobel Prize.

name: Jerry

line: No! It’s not fair. Everyone in this town got something they wanted from you, even Rick! I was your only friend, and I get nothing?

name: Needful
line: Okay, I’ll give you one thing. Name it.

name: Summer
line: I wanna help you.

name: Needful
line: Clever twist.

name: Summer
line: I learned from the best, you old fart. Now let’s go get you hydrated.

name: Rick
line: Looks like we’ve got… haunted boxing gloves that will make you the heavyweight champion, in 1936 and then you’ll be trapped there winning the same fight for eternity. I can take out the eternity, and the padding, and then you’ll have some time travelling mittens.

name: Rick
line: Oh, look, it’s Rosemary’s baby! How’s business?

name: Summer
line: Here’s the last of our inventory. We’re going to file chapter 11 and do some restructuring.

name: Rick
line: Sounds like code for ‘You win, Rick!’

name: Summer
line: That was important to you, wasn’t it?

name: Rick
line: Nope, it was important to your dumb devil friend. To me this was all just a bit like when Bugs Bunny fucks with the opera singer for twenty minutes.

name: Summer
line: He tried to kill himself.

name: Rick
line: Seriously? Holy crap. Holy crap.

name: Summer
line: But you know what, grandpa Rick? He’s strong. And he’s never going to give up.

name: Rick
line: Uh huh, yeah, I don’t care.

name: Summer
line: Oh, I know. Everyone knows you don’t care.

name: Rick
line: So?

name: Summer
line: So… have fun not caring.

name: Rick
line: I always do.

name: Summer
line: Good.

name: Rick
line: Yeah, it is good. It’s the best.

name: Summer
line: I’m sure it is. Bye.

name: Rick
line: Later!

name: Customer
line: I’m here to pick up my undead cat and child.

name: Rick
line: Yeah, uh, gimmie a sec.

name: Employee
line: These are the forms for the employee health plan.

name: Rick
line: Alright, yeah, uh, put ‘em on my… eh.

name: Rick
line: I just got bored. Everybody out.

name: Jerry
line: Alright, just one more rally, then I promise, we’ll get back to your science project.

name: Morty
line: Dad, Pluto isn’t a planet! It’s shrinking because of corporations!

name: Jerry
line: Yeah, that’s what that anti-planet nutjob Scroopy Noopers was screaming about outside the Ministry of Moneys fundraiser. Are you telling me four billion plutonians are wrong?

name: Morty
line: You told me science wasn’t easy!

name: Jerry
line: I said science isn’t always easy, obviously that means sometimes it is easy. Let’s not debase ourselves with word games, son.

name: Morty
line: Dad, their whole planet is dying!

name: Jerry
line: Hah! You called it a planet! Checkmate.

name: Jerry
line: What’s up, Pluto?

name: Plutonian woman
line: Mr. Smith, please! Tell my friend here what you just told me, go on.

name: Jerry
line: My Very Eager Mother Just Served Us Nine Pickles, and the pickles is Pluto.

name: Plutonian man
line: My god! The man’s a genius!

name: Morty
line: Um, excuse me?

name: Jerry
line: Morty, what?

name: Morty
line: Dad, what did you think about the recent report published by the Pluto Science Reader, linking plutoquakes, sinkholes and surface shrinkage to deep core plutonium drilling?

name: Jerry
line: ...Well son, what did you think when you were five, and you pooped your pants, and you threw your poopy undies out your bedroom window because you thought it was like throwing something in the garbage?

name: Jerry
line: I mean, I’m trimming the hedges and these things are just hanging there, was I supposed to think the poop bunny left them?

name: Morty
line: Good one, dad.

name: Rick
line: Hey Morty, you wanna go on a- oh.  Hey Beth? Hello?  Hey Jerry, you in here being stupid?

name: Rick
line: Thanks. Hey, y’know, I was thinking I might watch a movie…

name: Butter robot
line: I am not programmed for friendship.

name: Rick
line: Suit yourself.

name: Rick
line: Hey!  Hey. What’s going on?

name: Morty
line: Um… listen, can you help me do this stupid science fair project?

name: Rick
line: Whatever.

name: Flippynips
line: Jerry, you must be so excited! The Plutobell Prize is the highest honour a scientist can receive!

name: Jerry
line: I’m flattered, and humbled.

name: Flippynips
line: Ooh, I like that. Use that in your speech. Also, talk about Pluto being a planet, people like that.

name: Policeman
line: Your highness! We’ve captured Scroopy Noopers!

name: Scroopy Noopers
line: You animals! Animals!

name: Flippynips
line: Ooh, look whose little journey’s come to an end! Take him to Plutonimo Bay!

name: Scroopy Noopers
line: You can’t kill the truth, father!

name: Jerry
line: What?

name: Flippynips
line: I can see you’re confused. Plutonimo bay is a military prison, a sort of play on words-

name: Jerry
line: Did he call you father? Scroopy Noopers, the anti-planet nutjob is your son?

name: Flippynips
line: The young eat the old if you let them, Jerry. Pluto is a cold, cold celestial dwarf.

name: Jerry
line: It’s a what?

name: Flippynips
line: Huh? Oh- planet! Hah! Hoh, Pluto is a cold cold planet! That’s what I meant. Knock ‘em dead out there, you.

name: Jerry
line: Pluto is…

name: Jerry
line: Not a planet.

name: Crowd
line: Boo!

name: Jerry
line: Ow! It’s not a planet! Hey! It’s not a planet! I’m an idiot, and I love my son!

name: Needful
line: It’s been a long six hours, but we’ve overhauled Needful Things into the globally compliant, web 4.0 e-nomenon, n33dful.com! Spelled with 3s instead of Es.

name: Crowd
line: Woot! Yeah! Woot! Excited!

name: Needful
line: Okay, that’s it! We just got bought by Google!

name: Crowd
line: Yeah!

name: Summer
line: Mmh! I’m so proud of you, Lucius. So… how much did we make?

name: Needful
line: Haha. ‘We.’  This is my business! Security!

name: Summer
line: Ah! You’re Zuckerberging me?

name: Needful
line: I was Zuckerberging people before Zuckerberg’s balls dropped. I’m the devil, beeyotch! What what!

name: Jerry
line: Hey!

name: Jerry
line: Hey Morty.

name: Morty
line: Oh! Hey dad!  Um… What are you doing back from Pluto so quick?

name: Jerry
line: Ah, some people just can’t handle the truth. Especially dummies like me. Morty, I’m not as smart as your grandpa Rick, but I promise never to make that your problem again.

name: Morty
line: Hey, dad? Nobody’s smarter than Rick. But nobody else is my dad. You’re a genius at that.

name: Jerry
line: Wow… that’s humbling… and flattering, son. Thank you. What say we finish ourselves an 8-planet solar system?

name: Morty
line: Um… I’m just going to take this thing in and… get an A.

name: Butter robot
line: Butter.

name: Jerry
line: But-

name: Morty
line: You’re a genius at being my dad, dad. Quit while you’re ahead. And also, knock next time, you know? I mean, I’m sitting in here, I’m 14! I got a computer in here, you know!

name: Jerry
line: Oh. I uh- I think I underst-

name: Morty
line: You know you’re really playing with fire when you burst in here like that, man.

name: Jerry
line: I get it! Say no more.

name: Morty
line: I mean, one of these days, you know, you’re gonna, you’re gonna end up seeing something-

name: Jerry
line: I got it! Noted! Goodnight!

name: Rick
line: How’s your pretend grandpa doing AKA the devil?

name: Summer
line: He dumped me.

name: Rick
line: Oof, sorry.

name: Summer
line: Did we learn a lesson here I’m not seeing?

name: Rick
line: Hm, not sure.

name: Summer
line: Maybe in a much bigger way, Mr. Needful gave us both what we really wanted? Because I was always jealous of you hanging out with Morty and you didn’t realise how much you valued my approval?

name: Rick
line: No, that’s dumb.

name: Summer
line: Nah, not satisfying.

name: Rick
line: I’ll tell you what though, if it’s satisfaction you’re after, I think I might have an idea.

name: Summer
line: Uh huh… uh huh… uh huh totally let’s do it!

name: Needful
line: And that’s how I took my storefront into the forefront of the upfront! Thank you Seattle!

name: Needful
line: Rick? Summer?

name: Rick
line: Stupid mother-

name: Summer
line: Stupid bitch!

name: Rick
line: Stupid motherfucker!

name: Summer
line: Get some!

name: Rick
line: How do you like that! Augh! How do you like that?

name: Needful
line: Ugh… Why?

name: Summer
line: Because sometimes what you really need is for someone else to pay a horrible price.

name: Rick
line: We did it!

name: Summer
line: Haha, yeah bro. Yeah! Haha!

name: Rick
line: Was totally worth it! We did it, hahaha! We just pulled it off!

name: Summer
line: Yeah bro!

name: Rick
line: Hahaha!

name: Summer
line: Yeah.

name: Jerry
line: Last King Christmas last arrived!

name: Jerry
line: In the Christmas Christmas!  Mmm... Jerry, you are really giving it to this ham.

name: Jerry
line: Um, Merry Christmas?  Helloooo? My parents are coming over for the first time in years! Can we stow the gadgets and look alive?

name: Beth
line: Alive? For your parents?

name: Jerry
line: Good one.

name: Beth
line: Hey man!

name: Jerry
line: You ‘hey man’! This holiday is about humanity.

name: Morty
line: You know, I thought it was about being born half-God or something.

name: Jerry
line: Okay, whatever. All electronic items are going in the stocking. Now.

name: Morty
line: Ohhhh...

name: Summer
line: Dad, I'm not giving you my phone.

name: Jerry
line: Put it in the stocking, Summer, or I'm joining Facebook.

name: Rick
line: Ho ho ho, everybody.

name: Jerry
line: More like whoa whoa whoa. What is this? My parents are coming!

name: Rick
line: Calm down Jerry, this is Ruben, an old friend.

name: Ruben
line: Pearl Harbor.

name: Rick
line: I check in on him once a year and give him a little  medical  evaluation.

name: Beth
line: Aw, Dad... That is so sweet.

name: Jerry
line: Yeah, it is... I don't get it.

name: Ruben
line: Korea.

name: Rick
line: Don't worry about your C-C-Christmas, Jerry.  Ruben and I'll be in my workshop while you have another day in Phil Collins’ proverbial paradise.

name: Jerry
line: Huh. You think you know a guy.  Okay, there's my parents. Now remember, no TV, no phones, no laptops, we are connecting this Christmas, like old-school Jews on a Saturday.  Hey hey!

name: Leonard
line: Merry Christmas, son.

name: Jerry
line: Oh, hi. Can I help you?

name: Joyce
line: Jerry, this is Jacob.  Didn't you get our text message?

name: Beth, Summer, and Morty
line: No.

name: Jacob
line: You must be Jerry! That's a fine lookin’ apron. William Sonoma?

name: Jerry
line: I wish... But thank you.  So... you're a...friend of the family...?

name: Leonard
line: The way we see it, he's a part of the family.

name: Jerry
line: Wow!

name: Joyce
line: After your father's brush with cancer and losing your uncle, we looked at life and wondered how have we spent it? And how do we spend the rest of it? What are we going to be when we die? A list of fears and questions, or a collection of real experiences?

name: Beth
line: Holy crap, Joyce. That's amazing.

name: Leonard
line: Then Jacob came into our lives. We’re learning to live again.

name: Jacob
line: All three of us.

name: Jerry
line: ...Cool... Eggnog?

name: Jacob
line: Now we are talkin’! This man's got the apron and the eggnog, huh?

name: Rick
line: Hi Joyce, Leonard.  Hello there.

name: Jacob
line: Merry Christmas, man.

name: Rick
line: Morty! A moment of your time?

name: Rick
line: He's in bad shape, Morty.

name: Morty
line: Aw geez, Rick! What did you do?

name: Rick
line: Gee, thanks Morty. What kind of monster do you think I am? I-I'm sittin’ here trying to save the guy's life!  I want you to find Dr. Xenon Bloom. He'll know what's goin’ on.

name: Morty
line: Uh... W-W-Where do I find Dr. Bloom?

name: Rick
line: In Ruben.

name: Morty
line: Ruben... Minnesota?

name: Rick
line: Ruben on the table, Morty!  Look, I-I don't have time for you to wrap your little walnut around everything.  Hold your breath until the process is over or your lungs will collapse.

name: Morty
line: W-What proc—

name: Beth
line: Hey Dad, where's Morty?

name: Rick
line: He's busy.

name: Rick
line: Morty, can you hear me? Head North!

name: Morty
line: Rick... Where am I?

name: Rick
line: Depending on my aim, you should be just south of the entrance.

name: Morty
line: The entrance to what?

name: Rick
line: Welcome, Morty.  Welcome...  ...to Anatomy Park!

name: Rick
line: It's a little business venture I’ve been cookin’ up on the side with Dr. Bloom.  An amusement park inside a human body. Science isn't cheap, Morty. This should really help put a dent in the overhead.

name: Morty
line: Oh my God! This is insane! Spleen Mountain? Bladder Falls? Pirates of the Pancreas?

name: Rick
line: You got a problem with that last one, Morty?

name: Morty
line: Huh? No, no, I'm just reading them out loud in the order I'm seeing them.

name: Rick
line: Okay, alright, if I sounded a little defensive, it's because Pirates of the Pancreas was my baby.

name: Rick
line: I-I got a lot of push-back when I pitched it, Morty. I guess I'm still a little defensive. Let's just find Dr. Bloom, alright? I-I'm picking up a distress signal in the liver, Morty.

name: Rick
line: Proceed to the liver.

name: Automated voice
line: Arriving at ‘Liver’.

name: Morty
line: Ow!

name: Automated voice
line: Mind the gap.

name: Morty
line: It's really scary in here, Rick.

name: Rick
line: Liver's under maintenance. Ruben's seen some rough years, Morty. Don't judge. You don't agree to have a theme park built inside you if your life's going great.

name: Morty
line: OOOOHHH! Rick, it's a monster!

name: Rick
line: No no, Morty. The only monster here is alco—  —holism.  That is an animatronic werewolf.

name: Poncho
line: Who are you? Answer me! Where did you come from?

name: Morty
line: Mmm! M-M-My-my-my Grandpa Rick sent me!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Poncho! That's quite enough.

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Morty, that's Poncho.  This is Roger and Annie.

name: Morty
line: Oh...

name: Dr. Bloom
line: And I am Dr. Xenon Bloom.

name: Rick
line: Hey Bloom, it's Rick. What the hell's goin’ on here?

name: Dr. Bloom
line: I don't know why, but the entire security system has shut down. And I'm afraid the exhibits are unlocked.

name: Morty
line: Exhibits?

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Anatomy Park's greatest attraction, young man, isn't the music or the food or the Pirates of the Pancreas.

name: Rick
line: Watch it.

name: Dr. Bloom
line: It is first and foremost a living museum of humanity's most noble and ferocious diseases.

name: Morty
line: Diseases?!

name: Poncho
line: Hey Doc, I have news for ya.  Your living museum is officially a wild safari!

name: Roger
line: Hepatitis A! Run!

name: Jacob
line: Oh...  The food goes in your mouth, girl!

name: Jerry
line: Aha... I'm sorry Jacob, I guess I'm still confused about the precise nature and origin of your relationship with my parents. Are you like a—Are you like their caretaker? Is that what it is?

name: Joyce
line: We can go into detail later, son.

name: Leonard
line: Now wait, there, there's no point to secrecy. Let's all live and die honestly. Your mother and I have shared forty years of each other, mind, body, and soul.  And when minds and souls are joined for eternity, and when eternity is at the door, it's an invitation to let go of the body, and an opportunity to share and experiment.

name: Jerry
line: Dad, please, what are you saying?

name: Beth
line: Whatever it is, it's beautiful, Leonard.  And we support you.

name: Jerry
line: Speak for yourself! Because it, heheh, it sounds like you're about to say Jacob is your lover.

name: Leonard
line: No no no no.  Jacob is your mother's lover.  I watch them. Sometimes from a chair, sometimes from a closet. Almost always dressed as Superman.

name: Jacob
line: Oh...

name: Jacob
line: Jerry, this ham's got to be all you, right? It's in-cred-i-ble.

name: Summer
line: Happy human holiday, Dad.

name: Poncho
line: AHHHHHH!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Hepatitis won't follow us into the respiratory system!

name: Roger
line: That's strange...  Air flow is down twenty percent.

name: Dr. Bloom
line: So the brain isn't getting enough oxygen. That's why security is offline.

name: Morty
line: W-Well, I guess we better check it out.

name: Alexander
line: Hey, wait for me!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Put that back on!

name: Roger
line: If we got up to the bronchial catwalk, we could look for blockage.

name: Morty
line: I'll go.  Heheh...

name: Poncho
line: Don't be a hero, kid.

name: Morty
line: I'm not. I'm doin’ it because it's fun.

name: Poncho
line: We shouldn't be here.

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Whatever you do, don't fire that thing in here! We must save Ruben. This is my life's work.

name: Annie
line: Ah!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: It's alright, my dear. Nearly all human lungs contain a strain of this bacteria, but the scar tissue...  ...keeps them dormant.  Morty! Get down!

name: Morty
line: Whoa!  Whoa!

name: Morty
line: Oh! What are those things?!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Tuberculosis, coming in fast!

name: Poncho
line: Not faster than a bullet! Ahh!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: No! Do you know what you've done?!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Get to the digestive tract! He's coughing!

name: Alexander
line: Waaaah! Don't let me die!

name: Rick
line: Just take a deep breath, Ruben.

name: Morty
line: You're not gonna die! What's your name?

name: Alexander
line: My name is...  ALEXANDEEEEEEEER!

name: Morty
line: Rick! Ruben's got tuberculosis!

name: Rick
line: Oh, great work, Morty.  I'll just cure it, and then—

name: Rick
line: Okay. Well I can't cure death. This is bad, Morty. You're trapped in a dead man. Listen, if the situation keeps darkening, do yourself a favor—

name: Rick
line: —and hop by Pirates of the Pancreas. Obviously I'm biased, but, I think it's great, Morty.

name: Rick
line: It's a bunch of pirates runnin’ around a-a-a- pancreas. We don't whitewash it either, Morty. The pirates are really rapey. The top priority is to get you guys out of there, but I'm just saying, if that becomes impossible—

name: Rick
line: —please, you gotta treat yourself.

name: Morty
line: Geez, what's that horrible smell?

name: Dr. Bloom
line: You mean the Panda Express?  Kidding, I-I'm kidding.  The body is beginning to constrict and fill with gas. We’re inside a corpse, my boy. Anatomy Park is doomed.

name: Morty
line: Forget about the park, Doctor! How do we get out?!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: The digestive tract is the evacuation route. Get it? There's an emergency station in the colon with a ray that can enlarge us all.

name: Morty
line: Everybody! Get to the colon!

name: Poncho
line: Now I'm takin’ orders from a twelve-year-old boy?!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Morty. The scar sacs containing the tuberculosis were sabotaged. This disaster was an inside job. Keep your eyes on Annie. She was written up several times by her manager at the churro stand.

name: Roger
line: Intestines are ahead to the left. Then the right. Then left. Et cetera.

name: Morty
line: Hey, just so you know, I-I'm actually fourteen. So, you know...

name: Annie
line: What?

name: Morty
line: Not twelve.

name: Annie
line: Okay.

name: Morty
line: Because he just said I was twelve.

name: Annie
line: Oh. Good for you.

name: Rick
line: Oh. Oh, Morty. Strike one.

name: Morty
line: Nnn...

name: Animatronics
line: It's a road of laughter, a trail of food. It's a pathway that breaks up the fat in food. It's a tube in the chest and it sends out the rest. It's a small, small intestine!

name: Roger
line: It goes on like this for miles...

name: Dr. Bloom
line: And then we get to the large intestine!

name: Poncho
line: Shh.  I hear something.

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Don't move. Gonorrhea can't see us if we don't move.

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Wait! I was wrong! I was thinking of a T-rex.

name: Annie
line: We’re sitting ducks!

name: Morty
line: Doc! Didn't you say the body was filling up with gas?

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Yes. Why?

name: Poncho
line: Kid! You're a genius!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Are you mad?!

name: Morty
line: Everybody! In here!

name: Poncho
line: Hey Gonorrhea! How's this for a burning sensation?

name: Summer
line: Drummer, drum, drum, drum! Drummer, drum, drum drum drum, Christmas drums!

name: Leonard
line: Oh, Summer. Sing it! Haha.

name: Summer
line: Christmas drums being played by a boy!

name: Beth
line: Jerry, come on. This is what you wanted.

name: Jerry
line: I get it, Beth. Be careful what you wish for. I'm being punished for taking your iPad.

name: Beth
line: What? Jerry, let that stuff go, okay? I'm sorry I was a bitch earlier. Let's just be here.

name: Ethan
line: Ugh... Summer!

name: Summer
line: Ethan, what are you doing here?

name: Ethan
line: I’ve been texting you for hours. What the hell?!

name: Summer
line: I don't have my phone! I'm doing a human holiday!

name: Ethan
line: Did you even consider how that might make me feel?

name: Summer
line: How you feel? Why is everything always happening to you?!

name: Jerry
line: Summer, do you have a boyfriend?

name: Ethan
line: Yeah, do you, Summer?

name: Summer
line: I don't know Ethan, do I?

name: Jacob
line: Jerry, no disrespect, but you really need to connect more with your family, man.

name: Roger
line: I should be able to access the backup generator to get the growth ray back online. If it works, we'll be regular-sized in a few minutes. I just hope Ruben's not in a room with white carpets or upholstery.

name: Poncho
line: What the hell is that?

name: Dr. Bloom
line: The sphincter dam. We built it when Ruben became incontinent, but it was not designed to hold a corpse-load.

name: Roger
line: Almost got it. Everybody, move inside the circle!

name: Morty
line: Poncho? What is this in your backpack?

name: Dr. Bloom
line: That's bubonic plague! What are you doing with that, Poncho?

name: Poncho
line: Everybody get back!

name: Dr. Bloom
line: Poncho, you son of a bitch! You released the tuberculosis so you could steal from me?

name: Poncho
line: That's right, baby. A lot of people would pay top dollar to decimate the population. I'll take the highest bidder. Al Quaeda. North Korea. Republicans! Shriners! Balding men that work out! People on the Internet that are only turned on by cartoons of Japanese teenagers! Anything is better than working for you!  You pompous, negligent, iTunes Gift Card as a holiday bonus-giving—

name: Morty
line: AHHHHH!!!

name: Poncho
line: Ah! Eh! Get! Get off!  Ahhhh!

name: Annie
line: You guys!

name: Roger
line: It's gonna burst!  Go! Go, go, go!  My foot is stuck!

name: Annie
line: No!

name: Roger
line: This is okay! It's okay, just go! Tell my family I love them! They may be hard to find because my wife kept her last name and she made the kids take it too, so, I dunno, you could goo—

name: Annie
line: No!

name: Jacob
line: Let me ask you something Ethan. Where's the anger coming from, man?

name: Ethan
line: From Summer being a total bitch!

name: Jacob
line: Where's the anger coming from?

name: Ethan
line: ...My brother... took me fishing once...in the bushes...  I can't... I can't!  He made me feel like a girl!  I'm... m-made me a girl!

name: Jacob
line: He didn't make you anything, man. You are who you are.  She is who she is.  Now you go to her. Brand new.

name: Ethan
line: Come here right now!

name: Summer
line: Oh my god, I'm so sorry Ethan!  I love you!

name: Ethan
line: I love you so much.

name: Jerry
line: Um...

name: Joyce
line: You did it again, cubby. Come here.

name: Jerry
line: No! Stop! I hate this!

name: Joyce
line: Well, Christmas doesn't revolve around what you hate, son.

name: Jerry
line: Well then, I hate Christmas! Enjoy being human! You guys are gross and lame.

name: Animatronic Ruben
line: My name's Ruben Ridley. You're inside me right now, but by the end of this journey, I'll be inside all of you.

name: Animatronic Ruben
line: My story begins in the dot com crash in the early ‘90s.

name: Annie
line: You can put your fingers wherever you want…

name: Rick
line: Morty, you wanna put it on mute or something?

name: Rick
line: I’m trying to concentrate.

name: Jerry
line: Ah, Rick?

name: Rick
line: Not now, Jerry. I’ve got much, much smaller fish to fry.

name: Jerry
line: I wanted to say I’m sorry I ever judged you.  Right now, you’re my sanest relative.

name: Rick
line: Relative… That’s it! Relative size! Jerry, hand me a scalpel and a bundle of dynamite!  Morty! Can you get to the left nipple?

name: Morty
line: Are you kidding? I’m hoping I can get to both of them, Rick.

name: Rick
line: Morty, I’m talkin’ about Ruben's left nipple!
